    <refsection id="Description_DFLIPFLOP">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            That block outputs on <emphasis role="bold">Q</emphasis> its input state (<emphasis role="bold">D</emphasis>) when the enable input (<emphasis role="bold">en</emphasis>) is set
            and on the rising edge of the clock input (<emphasis role="bold">clk</emphasis>).
            The <emphasis role="bold">!Q</emphasis> output is the logical negation of <emphasis role="bold">Q</emphasis>.
            This flip-flop is also known as a delay flip-flop because the state of the input is modified
            only at the next rising edge of the clock.
        </para>
        <para>
            The D flip-flop is used as a basic cell of shift-registers.
        </para>
        <para>
            The truth table of this block is the following:
        </para>
        <para/>
        <informaltable border="1" cellpadding="3">
            <tr>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[\boldsymbol{clk}]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[\boldsymbol{en}]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[\boldsymbol{D}]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[\boldsymbol{Q_n}]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[\boldsymbol{!Q_n}]]></latex>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[\uparrow]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[0]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[X]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[Q_{n-1}]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[!Q_{n-1}]]></latex>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[\uparrow]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[1]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[0]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[0]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[1]]></latex>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[\uparrow]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[1]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[1]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[1]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[0]]></latex>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td align="left">Non-Rising</td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[X]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[X]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[Q_{n-1}]]></latex>
                </td>
                <td align="left">
                    <latex><![CDATA[!Q_{n-1}]]></latex>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </informaltable>
        <para>
            where
            <emphasis>
                <literal>X</literal>
            </emphasis>
            stands for "indifferent" and
            <emphasis><literal>
                    Q<subscript>n-1</subscript>
                </literal>
            </emphasis>
            is the previous output state of
            <emphasis><literal>
                    Q<subscript>n</subscript>
                </literal>
            </emphasis>
            .
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection id="Data_Type_DFLIPFLOP">
        <title>Data types</title>
        <para>
            The block supports the following types :
        </para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Inputs:
                </para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis role="bold">D</emphasis>: scalar. Scilab's int8 data type only.
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis role="bold">en</emphasis>: scalar. Scilab's real double.
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis role="bold">clk</emphasis>: scalar. Scilab's real double.
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
                <para>
                    A positive input is considered as logical 1, a negative or a null input as logical 0.
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Outputs : scalar. Scilab's int8 data type.
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </refsection>
